---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const structuredData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "Dashboard Guide - Fairmind Documentation",
  "description": "Learn how to use the Fairmind dashboard to monitor AI systems, view bias detection results, and manage model provenance.",
  "url": "https://fairmind.xyz/docs/dashboard"
};
---

<Layout 
  title="Dashboard Guide - Fairmind Documentation"
  description="Learn how to use the Fairmind dashboard to monitor AI systems, view bias detection results, and manage model provenance."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
        <div class="mb-4">
          <a href="/docs/fumadocs" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 font-medium">
            ← Back to Documentation
          </a>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Dashboard Guide</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700">
          Learn how to use the Fairmind dashboard to monitor your AI systems, view bias detection results, and manage model provenance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          The Fairmind dashboard is your central hub for AI governance and monitoring. It provides real-time insights into your AI systems' performance, fairness metrics, and compliance status.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Key Features</h3>
          <ul class="text-blue-800 space-y-2">
            <li>• Real-time bias detection monitoring</li>
            <li>• Model performance analytics</li>
            <li>• Compliance dashboard</li>
            <li>• Alert management</li>
            <li>• Model registry overview</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <p>
          When you first access the dashboard, you'll see an overview of all your registered AI models and their current status. The dashboard is organized into several key sections:
        </p>

        <h3>Main Dashboard</h3>
        <p>
          The main dashboard displays:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Model Overview:</strong> Total number of models, active models, and models requiring attention</li>
          <li><strong>Bias Detection Results:</strong> Recent bias analysis results and alerts</li>
          <li><strong>Performance Metrics:</strong> Model accuracy, fairness scores, and drift indicators</li>
          <li><strong>Recent Activity:</strong> Latest model updates, deployments, and alerts</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Navigation</h3>
        <p>
          Use the sidebar navigation to access different sections:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Dashboard:</strong> Main overview and metrics</li>
          <li><strong>Bias Detection:</strong> Detailed bias analysis tools and results</li>
          <li><strong>Models:</strong> Model registry and management</li>
          <li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> Real-time monitoring and alerting</li>
          <li><strong>Provenance:</strong> Model lineage and audit trails</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Dashboard Components</h2>
        
        <h3>Metrics Cards</h3>
        <p>
          The top of the dashboard displays key metrics in card format:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Total Models:</strong> Number of registered AI models</li>
          <li><strong>Active Models:</strong> Models currently in production</li>
          <li><strong>Bias Alerts:</strong> Number of active bias detection alerts</li>
          <li><strong>Compliance Score:</strong> Overall compliance rating</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Charts and Visualizations</h3>
        <p>
          Interactive charts help you visualize:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Bias detection trends over time</li>
          <li>Model performance comparisons</li>
          <li>Fairness metrics across different demographic groups</li>
          <li>Compliance status by model</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Best Practices</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Check the dashboard regularly for new alerts and insights</li>
          <li>Set up custom alerts for specific bias thresholds</li>
          <li>Use the filtering options to focus on specific models or time periods</li>
          <li>Export reports for stakeholder communication</li>
          <li>Review bias detection results before model deployments</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-900 mb-2">Note</h3>
          <p class="text-yellow-800">
            The dashboard is currently in development. Some features may not be fully functional in the MVP version.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2>Next Steps</h2>
        <p>
          Now that you understand the dashboard, explore these related guides:
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
          <a href="/docs/bias-detection" class="block p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:border-blue-300 hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Bias Detection Guide</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Learn how to detect and analyze bias in your AI models</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/docs/model-provenance" class="block p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:border-blue-300 hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Model Provenance</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Track model lineage and maintain audit trails</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
